JOHANNESBURG – Artists Miriam Makeba, Sipho ‘Hotstix’ Mabuse and Lillian Dube will be bestowed National Orders for their contribution to South Africa. Former deputy chief justice Dikgang Moseneke as well as sports stars Hashim Amla and Elana Meyer also made the cut. Ex-Liberian President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf and former Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano will also be honoured. Other notable honours that will be bestowed posthumously, including that of struggle activists Mary Fitzgerald and Rahima Moosa. Classification: #NationalOrders are the highest awards that SA bestows, through the President of the Republic, upon citizens & members of the international community who have contributed meaningfully towards making the country a free, democratic and successful nation, united in its diversity. pic.twitter.com/UAwTyBkzOE Full list: #NationalOrders The Order of Ikhamanga: recognises South African citizens who have excelled in the fields of arts, culture, literature, music, journalism and sport. The Order will be bestowed in Silver on: pic.twitter.com/2bBv8iY7Th #NationalOrders The Order of the Baobab in Silver will be bestowed on: pic.twitter.com/E3Ltzxt8eB #NationalOrders The Order of Luthuli will be bestowed in Bronze to: pic.twitter.com/OLNXBR1DTg #NationalOrders The Order of Luthuli will be bestowed in Silver to: pic.twitter.com/4emSQNV6ph #NationalOrders The Order of Luthuli will be bestowed in Gold to: pic.twitter.com/C84A3bazT6 #NationalOrders The Order of Luthuli will be bestowed in Gold to: pic.twitter.com/C84A3bazT6 #NationalOrders The Order of the Companions of OR Tambo in Silver will be bestowed on: pic.twitter.com/ovAbfHBMQC #NationalOrders The Order of the Companions of OR Tambo in Gold will be bestowed on: pic.twitter.com/RHmmkFspt9 eNCA